<dl id="n54145f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54145f">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54145f"> 145(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Eriguru <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n54145f"><li>FW 279.03 </li><li><a href="../../flex/lf/lexlf.htm#n54145f">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/lf/l39lf.htm#n54145f">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n54145f">MS BL 47478-339</ms> </li><li>JJA 53:318 <a name="lad13" href="../../ff/fdra/lda.htm#lfd4">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/lf/lfd4.htm#n54145f">Draft: II.2&sect;7.4</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">J&apos;avais donc la confirmation de ce que j&apos;avais entendu depuis longtemps &agrave; Houa&iuml;lou, que la pri&egrave;re aux anc&ecirc;tres n&apos;&eacute;tait pas excessivement ancienne, et que <mark>Eriguru</mark>, le fondateur du clan Eriguru, &eacute;tait le premier qui avait cess&eacute; de prier les montagnes pour s&apos;adresser aux anc&ecirc;tres. <br><font color="green">[So I had confirmation of what I had heard for a long time in Houa&iuml;lou, that the prayer to the ancestors was not excessively old, and that Eriguru, the founder of the Eriguru clan, was the first who had stopped praying the mountains to address the ancestors.]</font> <small> Lucian L&eacute;vy-Bruhl, <a name="LBEM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LBEM"><cite title="source">L'exp&eacute;rience mystique</cite></a> (1938) 182</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
